$lang['How do you convert a Hexadecimal to a Decimal?'] = 'Uyiguqula kanjani i-Hexadecimal ibe idesimali?';
$lang['When converting hexadecimal to decimal, the first step is to divide the hex number by 16. This will give you the base number. The second step is to divide each digit of the hex number by 16 and write down the results. Finally, add up all of the numbers that were just calculated.'] = 'Lapho uguqula i-hexadecimal ibe idesimali, isinyathelo sokuqala ukuhlukanisa inombolo ye-hex ngo-16. Lokhu kuzokunikeza inombolo yesisekelo. Isinyathelo sesibili siwukuhlukanisa idijithi ngayinye yenombolo ye-hex ngo-16 bese ubhala phansi imiphumela. Ekugcineni, hlanganisa zonke izinombolo ezisanda kubalwa.';
$lang['For example, if someone wants to convert 9F7A to decimal, they would first divide 9F7A by 16 which equals 6051. Then they would divide each digit of 6051 by 16 which equals 381. Lastly, they would add up 381 + 381 + 381 which equals 1144. Therefore, 9F7A in decimal is equal to 1144'] = 'Isibonelo, uma umuntu efuna ukuguqula u-9F7A abe yidesimali, bazoqale bahlukanise u-9F7A ngo-16 olingana no-6051. Bese behlukanisa idijithi ngayinye ka-6051 ngo-16 elingana no-381. Okokugcina, bazohlanganisa 381 + 381 + 381 okulingana 1144. Ngakho-ke, u-9F7A ngedesimali ulingana no-1144';
$lang['How do you convert a Decimal to a Hexadecimal?'] = 'Uyiguqula kanjani idesimali ibe iHexadecimal?';
$lang['Converting decimal to hexadecimal is a simple process, and can be done with a calculator or online converter. In order to convert the number, divide it by 16 and take the remainder. This remainder will then correspond to a hexadecimal digit. For example, if you have the decimal number 234, divide it by 16 and take the remainder: 234 / 16 = 14 R 2. Therefore, in hexadecimal notation, this number would be written as “E2”.'] = 'Ukuguqula idesimali ibe i-hexadecimal kuyinqubo elula, futhi ingenziwa ngesibali noma isiguquli esiku-inthanethi. Ukuze uguqule inombolo, ihlukanise ngo-16 bese uthatha okusele. Lokhu okusele kuzobe sekuhambisana nedijithi ye-hexadecimal. Isibonelo, uma unenombolo yedesimali engu-234, yehlukanise ngo-16 bese uthatha esele: 234/16 = 14 R 2. Ngakho-ke, ku-hexadecimal notation, le nombolo izobhalwa ngokuthi “E2”.';
$lang['There are many tools available online that can help with converting between decimal and hexadecimal numbers. Additionally, most calculators have a built-in function that will allow you to do this conversion very easily. With just a few clicks of the mouse or taps on the keyboard, you’ll be able to change any decimal value into its corresponding hexadecimal equivalent!'] = 'Kunamathuluzi amaningi atholakalayo ku-inthanethi angasiza ekuguquleni phakathi kwezinombolo zedesimali kanye ne-hexadecimal. Ukwengeza, ama-calculator amaningi anomsebenzi owakhelwe ngaphakathi ozokuvumela ukuthi wenze lokhu kuguqulwa kalula kakhulu. Ngokuchofoza okumbalwa nje kwegundane noma ukuthepha kukhibhodi, uzokwazi ukushintsha noma yiliphi inani ledesimali lilingane ne-hexadecimal yalo ehambisanayo!';
$lang['What are the benefits of using a Hexadecimal over a Decimal?'] = 'Yiziphi izinzuzo zokusebenzisa i-Hexadecimal ngaphezu kwedesimali?';
$lang['The hexadecimal, or base-16, system was designed to emulate some of the same properties as the decimal system. In other words, it was created to make things easier for us humans. The number 423 has 16 digits instead of 10 digits available in a decimal system. This is because hexadecimal uses a base of 16 symbols instead of 10. After F, the order begins again with 0 and so on and so forth until we get to 15 which is notated as F.'] = 'I-hexadecimal, noma i-base-16, isistimu yaklanywa ukulingisa ezinye izici ezifanayo nesistimu yedesimali. Ngamanye amazwi, yadalelwa ukwenza izinto zibe lula kithina bantu. Inombolo 423 inezinombolo eziyi-16 esikhundleni samadijithi ayi-10 atholakala ohlelweni lwedesimali. Lokhu kungenxa yokuthi i-hexadecimal isebenzisa isisekelo sezimpawu eziyi-16 esikhundleni sika-10. Ngemva kuka-F, i-oda liqala futhi ngo-0 njalo njalo njalonjalo size sifike ku-15 okuphawulwe ngokuthi F.';
$lang['Hexadecimal encoding reduces the number of digits by a factor of eight when compared to the decimal system. Additionally, hexadecimal numbers have an information density that is twice as high as decimal numbers do. So, why should you bother learning this funky little numbering scheme? Because it can make your life easier! When working with digital systems or data transmission, using hex will save you time and energy when decoding cryptic messages or data streams.'] = 'Umbhalo wekhodi we-hexadecimal kunciphisa inani lamadijithi nge-factory yesishiyagalombili uma kuqhathaniswa nesistimu yedesimali. Ukwengeza, izinombolo ze-hexadecimal zinomthamo wolwazi ophindwe kabili kunezinombolo zamadesimali. Ngakho-ke, kungani kufanele uzihluphe ngokufunda lesi sikimu sezinombolo esincane esijabulisayo? Ngoba kungenza ukuphila kwakho kube lula! Uma usebenza ngamasistimu edijithali noma ukudluliswa kwedatha, ukusebenzisa i-hex kuzokongela isikhathi namandla lapho ubhala imilayezo eyimfihlo noma ukusakazwa kwedatha.';
$lang['What are the benefits of using a Decimal over a Hexadecimal?'] = 'Yiziphi izinzuzo zokusebenzisa idesimali ngaphezu kwe-Hexadecimal?';
$lang['When it comes to binary coding, Hexadecimal is more efficient because it reduces 8 digits to 2. Additionally, Hex provides a greater degree of information density and higher accuracy in numbers than binary does. This is due to the fact that Hex uses 16 symbols instead of just two like binary. Because of this increased efficiency, Hexadecimal is often used when binary coding in computing and digital electronics as well as for computer science applications.'] = 'Uma kuziwa ekubhalweni kwekhodi kanambambili, i-Hexadecimal isebenza kahle kakhulu ngoba yehlisa amadijithi ayi-8 kuya ku-2. Ukwengeza, i-Hex inikeza izinga elikhulu lokuminyana kolwazi nokunemba okuphezulu kwezinombolo kunezimbambambili. Lokhu kungenxa yokuthi i-Hex isebenzisa izimpawu eziyi-16 esikhundleni sezibili nje ezifana kanambambili. Ngenxa yalokhu kusebenza kahle okukhulayo, i-Hexadecimal ivamise ukusetshenziswa lapho kufakwa amakhodi kanambambili ku-computing kanye ne-digital electronics kanye nasezinhlelweni zesayensi yekhompyutha.';
$lang['In addition, Hexadecimal takes up less space than decimal. With only two digits instead of 8 binary digits, Hex numbers represent large numbers much more concisely. This can be very helpful when working with computer systems, as there is less chance for mistakes when typing in hex codes compared to decimal codes which have so many decimal points all over the place!'] = 'Ngaphezu kwalokho, i-Hexadecimal ithatha isikhala esincane kunedesimali. Ngamadijithi amabili kuphela esikhundleni samadijithi kanambambili ayi-8, izinombolo ze-Hex zimele izinombolo ezinkulu ngokufingqiwe. Lokhu kungaba usizo kakhulu uma usebenza nezinhlelo zekhompiyutha, njengoba mancane amathuba okuba amaphutha uma uthayipha amakhodi e-hex uma kuqhathaniswa namakhodi wedesimali anamaphuzu amaningi wedesimali kuyo yonke indawo!';
$lang['What is the range of values that can be represented by a Hexadecimal?'] = 'Yibuphi ububanzi bamanani obungamelwa i-Hexadecimal?';
$lang['A hexadecimal number is a number that uses 16 digits instead of the 10 digits we use in the decimal system. This number system is called base-16, and it helps us to emulate the properties of our familiar decimal system. In hexadecimal, each digit represents a power of 16. The numbers 0 through 9 represent the powers of 1 through 10, while A through F represent the powers of 11 through 15.'] = 'Inombolo ye-hexadecimal iyinombolo esebenzisa amadijithi ayi-16 esikhundleni samadijithi ayi-10 esiwasebenzisa ohlelweni lwedesimali. Le sistimu yezinombolo ibizwa nge-base-16, futhi isisiza ukuthi silingise izici zesistimu yethu yedesimali ejwayelekile. Ku-hexadecimal, idijithi ngayinye imelela amandla angu-16. Izinombolo 0 kuya ku-9 zimelela amandla ka-1 kuya ku-10, kuyilapho u-A ukuya ku-F amelela amandla ka-11 kuya ku-15.';
$lang['Just like in decimal, after 16 symbols have been used in Hexadecimal, the order of numbers starts over again at zero. So, hexadecimal 10 is equal to decimal 16, and hexadecimal 11 is equal to decimal 17. And so on!'] = 'Njengakudesimali, ngemva kokusetshenziswa kwezimpawu eziyi-16 ku-Hexadecimal, ukuhleleka kwezinombolo kuqala futhi kokuthi ziro. Ngakho-ke, i-hexadecimal 10 ilingana nedesimali 16, futhi i-hexadecimal 11 ilingana nedesimali 17. Futhi njalo!';
$lang['What is the range of values that can be represented by a Decimal?'] = 'Ibuphi ububanzi bamanani obungamelwa idesimali?';
$lang['The Decimal system starts with 10 and goes up to 15. This means that the range of values that can be represented by a decimal number is from 0-9, followed by A-F (10-15).'] = 'Isistimu yedesimali iqala ngo-10 futhi ikhuphuke iye ku-15. Lokhu kusho ukuthi ububanzi bamanani obungamelwa inombolo yedesimali busuka ku-0-9, bulandelwe yi-AF (10-15).';
$lang['How do you decode Hexadecimal?'] = 'Uyinquma kanjani i-Hexadecimal?';
$lang['When it comes to decoding Hexadecimal, there are a few things you need to know. First, just like the decimal system, the hexadecimal system has 10 symbols (0-9) that represent numbers. However, in hexadecimal, these digits have values that are twice as large as their counterparts in the decimal system. So, while the number “10” is represented by the symbol “A” in hexadecimal, it would be equal to “10” in the decimal system.'] = 'Uma kukhulunywa ngokuqopha i-Hexadecimal, kunezinto ezimbalwa okudingeka uzazi. Okokuqala, njengesistimu yedesimali, isistimu ye-hexadecimal inezimpawu eziyi-10 (0-9) ezimele izinombolo. Nokho, ku-hexadecimal, lawa madijithi anamanani amakhulu ngokuphindwe kabili kunozakwabo ohlelweni lwedesimali. Ngakho, ngenkathi inombolo “10” imelelwa uphawu “A” ku-hexadecimal, izolingana no-“10” ohlelweni lwedesimali.';
$lang['Similarly, after reaching 9 in Hexadecimal (represented by “F”), we start counting again at 10 (“10”). This pattern continues until we reach 15 (“1F”), at which point we reset back to 0 and begin counting again at 16 (“20”). This might sound confusing at first, but with a little practice, it will become second nature!'] = 'Ngokufanayo, ngemva kokufinyelela ku-9 ku-Hexadecimal (emelwe ngu-“F”), siqala ukubala futhi ku-10 (“10”). Le phethini iyaqhubeka size sifike ku-15 (“1F”), ngaleso sikhathi sisetha kabusha sibuyele ku-0 bese siqala ukubala futhi ngo-16 (“20”). Lokhu kungase kuzwakale kudida ekuqaleni, kodwa ngokuzijwayeza okuncane, kuzoba imvelo yesibili!';
